@Mod_Adam wrote:

Telenim:

Nice speech Adam but I don’t think that’s gonna happen

Need an example?

I was an asshole to my younger brother for years. Sometimes I can’t even remember the good that I did. I used to make fun of him non-stop: about his weight, his eating habits, his social life. I changed the way he acted; not only around me, but his friends, my family, etc. Luckily, thank the Lord, I’ve matured and have realized that I can’t change what I’ve done, but I can change what I will do. Finally, my brother is old enough to realize that I am sorry and that I really want to set an example that an older brother should. I am thankful that he’s forgiven me. I love him.
